00:57:46.070 --> 00:57:47.370
&gt;&gt; Jonathan Loar:
So we'll open it

00:57:47.370 --> 00:57:49.960
up to questions if
anybody has any.

00:57:54.770 --> 00:57:56.070
&gt;&gt; Richard Solomon: Please.

00:57:56.070 --> 00:57:57.370
Yes.

00:57:57.370 --> 00:57:58.670
&gt;&gt; I have a question.

00:57:58.670 --> 00:58:01.430
Could you just say something
about how the manuscripts,

00:58:01.430 --> 00:58:07.460
I mean how we get manuscripts,
how [inaudible] manuscripts?

00:58:07.460 --> 00:58:13.670
&gt;&gt; Richard Solomon: Yes, that's
a little bit complicated.

00:58:13.670 --> 00:58:18.800
The problem is that in nearly
all cases we don't really know

00:58:18.800 --> 00:58:20.570
where the manuscripts come from

00:58:20.570 --> 00:58:23.070
and that's why I
didn't talk about that.

00:58:23.070 --> 00:58:26.690
Almost all of the manuscripts
of this type have come

00:58:26.690 --> 00:58:31.150
up through private collections
or antiquities market

00:58:31.150 --> 00:58:34.880
and that is frankly
a murky place.

00:58:34.880 --> 00:58:41.590
The people who have possession
of them may or may not know

00:58:41.590 --> 00:58:45.590
where they actually came from
and they may or may not tell you

00:58:45.590 --> 00:58:48.950
or may or may not
tell you the truth.

00:58:48.950 --> 00:58:55.490
But what we do know fairly
certainly is that some,

00:58:55.490 --> 00:59:02.090
probably most, maybe all of them
were originally in clay pots

00:59:02.090 --> 00:59:04.740
and we actually have not here

00:59:04.740 --> 00:59:07.160
but in the British Library
we actually have one

00:59:07.160 --> 00:59:09.300
of the clay pots
in which they came.

00:59:09.300 --> 00:59:13.900
And these pots were buried
probably under stupas

00:59:13.900 --> 00:59:17.260
or near stupas in a monastery.

00:59:17.260 --> 00:59:20.300
So they put the manuscripts
in the pots,

00:59:20.300 --> 00:59:24.970
sealed it up with a kind of,
I think probably with beeswax,

00:59:24.970 --> 00:59:31.500
put a lid on it and sealed it,
and they buried it in the stupa.

00:59:31.500 --> 00:59:36.150
At least some of those came
from Hadda, in Afghanistan

00:59:36.150 --> 00:59:38.520
if you're familiar with that.

00:59:38.520 --> 00:59:40.940
They all come --
They probably --

00:59:40.940 --> 00:59:43.460
All of most of them come
from eastern Afghanistan,

00:59:43.460 --> 00:59:46.930
maybe from some northwestern
Pakistan.

00:59:46.930 --> 00:59:53.270
And so that's -- Unfortunately,
that's all we really know.

00:59:53.270 --> 00:59:58.970
There are no cases where we
have any of these manuscripts

00:59:58.970 --> 01:00:03.170
and know specifically definitely
exactly where they came from

01:00:03.170 --> 01:00:10.130
but we have some general
knowledge about the provenance.

01:00:10.130 --> 01:00:13.300
It's a problem.

01:00:13.300 --> 01:00:17.230
Yes, please.

01:00:18.510 --> 01:00:51.820
[ Inaudible Audience Question ]

01:00:51.820 --> 01:00:55.850
Yes. You may be referring to
in Buddhist literature they,

01:00:55.850 --> 01:01:03.220
in [inaudible], they talk about
Taxila, which was the great city

01:01:03.220 --> 01:01:06.110
of that area, and they
call it the university

01:01:06.110 --> 01:01:08.700
but that's actually kind of an
anachronism and that's something

01:01:08.700 --> 01:01:14.720
that modern scholars, modern
translators have used that term

01:01:14.720 --> 01:01:18.910
but really it was just kind
of center of learning but not

01:01:18.910 --> 01:01:23.350
in a formal sense
of a university.

01:01:23.350 --> 01:01:28.280
But in terms of propagation,
well we don't know very much

01:01:28.280 --> 01:01:31.630
about that but there's one very
important point that we do know

01:01:31.630 --> 01:01:35.980
and that concerns what I
mentioned briefly before,

01:01:35.980 --> 01:01:38.660
the transmission
of this material,

01:01:38.660 --> 01:01:41.060
I mean Buddhist literature
in general,

01:01:41.060 --> 01:01:45.740
into Central Asia
and into China.

01:01:45.740 --> 01:01:50.630
So there's something called
the Gandhari hypothesis

01:01:50.630 --> 01:01:53.090
which I didn't talk about
but I will for a minute

01:01:53.090 --> 01:01:54.820
because it's relevant
to your question.

01:01:54.820 --> 01:01:59.570
This is something that actually
goes back to I think the 1930s.

01:01:59.570 --> 01:02:04.960
It was first noticed that
if you look at some types

01:02:04.960 --> 01:02:07.370
of Chinese Buddhist
texts and, of course,

01:02:07.370 --> 01:02:11.560
Chinese Buddhist texts are, the
[inaudible] are all translated

01:02:11.560 --> 01:02:15.170
from Indian originals.

01:02:15.170 --> 01:02:17.880
And this was a huge
enterprise that went

01:02:17.880 --> 01:02:21.930
on from the second
century BC for, I'm sorry,

01:02:21.930 --> 01:02:24.710
second century AD
for a thousand years.

01:02:24.710 --> 01:02:26.620
It was this enormous project

01:02:26.620 --> 01:02:29.860
of translating the Buddhist
scriptures into Chinese.

01:02:29.860 --> 01:02:32.360
It's actually the biggest

01:02:32.360 --> 01:02:37.100
and most impressive
translation project

01:02:37.100 --> 01:02:38.430
in the history of the world.

01:02:38.430 --> 01:02:41.500
I'll go out on a
limb and say that.

01:02:41.500 --> 01:02:44.880
Very few people outside
Buddha circles know that

01:02:44.880 --> 01:02:51.710
but it's a major achievement in
world civilization I would say.

01:02:51.710 --> 01:02:56.530
Now concerning that, there was
this idea called the Gandhari

01:02:56.530 --> 01:02:59.600
hypothesis and what happened
is that certain text scholars,

01:02:59.600 --> 01:03:04.270
philologists were looking at
the early Chinese translations,

01:03:04.270 --> 01:03:07.500
second, third, maybe
fourth century,

01:03:07.500 --> 01:03:12.910
and looking at how they
rendered the Indian names.

01:03:12.910 --> 01:03:15.520
And this was a problem
because Indian names

01:03:15.520 --> 01:03:18.260
and Chinese names are extremely
different in the structure

01:03:18.260 --> 01:03:21.700
of the language and the
sound system are so different

01:03:21.700 --> 01:03:23.920
and the writing system,
everything is different,

01:03:23.920 --> 01:03:25.660
so they struggled

01:03:25.660 --> 01:03:32.330
with representing Buddhist
Indian names in Chinese but some

01:03:32.330 --> 01:03:36.780
of these early scholars noted
that there were maybe oddities

01:03:36.780 --> 01:03:39.860
in the way that the
names were presented

01:03:39.860 --> 01:03:44.520
which made them question
what had been assumed,

01:03:44.520 --> 01:03:47.800
which it was assumed that the
Chinese translations were made

01:03:47.800 --> 01:03:50.740
from Sanskrit but
certain of the features

01:03:50.740 --> 01:03:54.030
of the names actually
didn't line up with Sanskrit

01:03:54.030 --> 01:03:59.600
but they do line up with
the corresponding Gandhari

01:03:59.600 --> 01:04:02.400
pronunciations, like
that slide I showed you

01:04:02.400 --> 01:04:05.960
where you'd see the
different sound systems.

01:04:05.960 --> 01:04:10.170
So the Gandhari hypothesis
then was

01:04:10.170 --> 01:04:15.840
that the Chinese Buddhist
texts, not all of them

01:04:15.840 --> 01:04:18.570
but the early phase,
were actually based not

01:04:18.570 --> 01:04:21.780
on Sanskrit originals but
on Gandhari originals.

01:04:21.780 --> 01:04:25.800
And one of the question
marks about that theory was

01:04:25.800 --> 01:04:28.490
at the time and for decades
afterwards there were no

01:04:28.490 --> 01:04:29.790
Gandhari text.

01:04:29.790 --> 01:04:32.130
Now to make a long
story short, there are

01:04:32.130 --> 01:04:39.500
and so this new material
definitely supports,

01:04:39.500 --> 01:04:42.720
I would say proves the
Gandhari hypothesis.

01:04:42.720 --> 01:04:48.330
So that's really, coming back to
your question, the propagation,

01:04:48.330 --> 01:04:52.200
the historically
important propagation is

01:04:52.200 --> 01:04:54.890
that these were brought
by various people

01:04:54.890 --> 01:04:57.610
into China and translated.

01:04:57.610 --> 01:05:00.770
They probably wasn't
propagated in India proper

01:05:00.770 --> 01:05:02.320
because in India proper,

01:05:02.320 --> 01:05:06.140
the other regions had their
own corresponding sets of texts

01:05:06.140 --> 01:05:10.390
in their own local
languages and dialects.

01:05:10.390 --> 01:05:11.840
I hope I answered your question.

01:05:11.840 --> 01:05:15.030
Yes, please.

